  <thing id="cMPSGGHtoK" name="Hard to Kill" description="The tough doesn&apos;t pass out or die when other people do. The tough remains conscious but disabled up to a number of negative hp equal to their Con bonus or 1/4 class level, whichever is higher (minimum 1). \n\nThis is instead of being disabled when at 0 hp and unconscious at negative hp values.\n\nA tough also doesn&apos;t die when reaching a negative hp total equal to their constitution, instead adding their Con bonus or 1/4 their class level, whichever is higher, to the negative hp total they can reach before dying.\n\nMassive Damage: A tough with this talent also does not die from massive damage, if this rule is in use." compset="CustomSpec" summary="The tough doesn&apos;t pass out or die when other people do." uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>Anachronistic Adventurers - The Tough

Super Genius Games
www.supergeniusgames.com</comment>
    <usesource source="MPRGGAnac"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="arMPSGGTou" name="Tough" abbrev="Tough"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="Secondary"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="arMSRDToug"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var uncons as number
var death as number
var levelquart as number

levelquart = field[xTotalLev].value / 4
levelquart = round(levelquart, 0, -1)

if (levelquart < 1) then
    levelquart = 1
endif

if (levelquart < hero.child[aCON].field[aModBonus].value) then 
    uncons = hero.child[aCON].field[aModBonus].value
    death = hero.child[aCON].field[aModBonus].value + hero.child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value
else
    uncons = levelquart
    death = levelquart + hero.child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value
endif

field[livename].text = field[thingname].text & " (Unconscious: -" & uncons & " | Death: -" & death & ")"

#situational[hero.child[aCON], "Unconscious at -" & uncons & ". Dead at -" & death, field[thingname].text]]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMPSGGIYFc" name="In Your Face" description="Having a tough attack you can be distracting, making it difficult to take careful actions. When the tough makes a full attack routine, that foe suffers a penalty to attack rolls, skill and ability checks, and save DCs of all spells and effects.\n\nThe base penelty is -2.\n\nThis must be melee attacks and all directed at a single foe This effect lasts until the beginning of the tough&apos;s next turn. These penalties increase by -1 every 8 levels." compset="CustomSpec" summary="Foe suffers a penalty to attack rolls, skill checks, ability checks" uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>Anachronistic Adventurers - The Tough

Super Genius Games
www.supergeniusgames.com</comment>
    <usesource source="MPRGGAnac"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="arMPSGGTou" name="Tough" abbrev="Tough"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="Secondary"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="arMSRDToug"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[var levelquart as number

levelquart = field[xTotalLev].value / 8
levelquart = round(levelquart, 0, -1)
~ Base penelty value of 2
levelquart += 2

field[livename].text = field[thingname].text & " (-" & levelquart & " Penalty)"]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMPSGGMTHl" name="Madder Than Hell" description="Whenever the tough is subject to one of the following conditions, they gain a +2 bonus to their attack rolls, damage, armor class, and saving throws: blinded, confused, dazed, shaken, sickened, or staggered. \n\nThe worse things are, the madder (and more dangerous) the tough gets.\n\nIf for some reason the tough can ignore or reduce the penalties from the triggering condition, they do not receive their madder than hell bonus." compset="CustomSpec" summary="+2 Bonus to attack, damage, ac, saving throws; under certain conditions" uniqueness="unique">
